    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Places designed for those with decreased cognizance from conditions such as Alzheimer's disease. These combine residential, commercial, and “public” buildings where residents live and associate with others in environments resembling pre-industrial small towns that include pedestrian-friendly navigation routes, family-centered houses, and shared communal spaces. Healthcare facilities are often disguised.</Note_Text>
